ortionality of rule enforcement.<br>
<br>
If a child fears you because you beat the tar out of them when they do wrong -- you are just as much a worthless parent as someone who sends a kid to time out when they pull a knife on someone.<br>
<br>
The macho nonsense that you have to strike a child to enforce discipline is crap.  I do not lump a swat on a 2 year old's bottom to grab its attention in this catagory.  I am talking about a child old enough to reason and understand consequences.<br>
<br>
The idea that you can reason with a toddler or small child is equal crap<br>
<br>
Fear does not raise a healthy society, but neither does lassazie faire(sp?) parenting with parents who think taking away TV privildges will cure all bad behavior.  Rules should be and must be enforced.<br>
<br>
To quoute Isaac Asimov: &quot;Violence is the last refuge of the incompetent.&quot;    There are far more insidous ways to grab and keep your kids attention. Balance is always the key<br>
<br>
<br>
Bubba<br>
