*edit to explain myself more* <br>
There are numerous warning signs for a child with violent tendencies, depression etc.  <br>
Taking a class or reading books on parenting before you have kids is not only a good idea but it SHOULD be the law. <br>
<br>
If you cannot be objective enough to notice your childs cry for help (no matter how unconscious it is to them) then you should not be a parent.  A child that can justify something of this magnitude HAD to give signs, unless hes like a comic book villain born knowing he is evil and that society doesnt accept it. If your going to go with the villain route we might as well add in a possible alien abduction.<br>
<br>
<br>
I dunno, I guess I see things pretty cut and dry which doesnt allow for mistakes to be the 1% of possibilities. <br>
Either the parents effed up and the child wipes out a bunch of people (or himself) or they dont, and the kid goes away where he can work on his problems without harming himself and others.<br>
<br>
There really is no excuse for the first, the only excuse that can be used is &quot;I didnt know he would do something like that.&quot; <br>
Well, why the hell didnt you Mommy??  <br>
An excuse is just an admitted mistake.<br>
