Are they born evil? No<br>
<br>
Personally I do not believe anyone is born with an evil nature. The way they are nurtured or lack there of, can determine if they become evil even at a young age.<br>
<br>
If a child has signs of an agressive personality or a violent personality then it is up to the parents to recognize this and seek out ways of correcting it (this means early on, not when it may be too late).<br>
<br>
The comment of how all parents think thier kid is cute or smart or whatever does not hold up well. Of course Parents are going to think these things and they should. But a good parents does not let thier love blind them to the needs of thier child. Behavior needing corrected is a need. Being in tune with your child is a need.<br>
<br>
There are parents who see neggative behavior and write it off as &quot;Oh he is just being a kid&quot; or &quot;he is going through a stage&quot; and that is a parent who uses those as excuses to escape from thier responsibilites. Being a parent is not easy. <p>Crackanna Breeze<BR>
